comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-05T20:40:04.278Z",claude-code-agent,"Sub-agent starting: src/core/history/history-storage-stats.ts — pure aggregate of history streams (total streams/lines/bytes, top-N largest+deepest, global oldest/newest). Orchestrator wires into pm stats --storage."
  "2026-06-05T20:44:07.560Z",claude-code-agent,"Sub-agent DONE: history-storage-stats.ts implemented and tested.\n\n**Exported signature:**\n- `HistoryStreamStat { id, bytes, lines, oldest_ts: string|null, newest_ts: string|null }`\n- `HistoryStorageEntryRef { id, ts }`\n- `HistoryStorageStats { total_streams, total_lines, total_bytes, largest_by_bytes, deepest_by_lines, oldest_entry, newest_entry }`\n- `computeHistoryStorageStats(streams, options?): HistoryStorageStats`\n\n**Behavior decisions:**\n- topN defaults to 5; `Math.max(0, Math.floor(topN))` clamps negatives to 0 and floors fractional values. topN=0 returns empty arrays for both top-N fields.\n- Unparseable JSON lines: counted toward `lines` total but ts is skipped for min/max tracking.\n- Lines with missing or non-string `ts` field: counted as lines, skipped for ts.\n- Invalid date strings (Date.parse → NaN): skipped for ts tracking.\n- CRLF line endings supported via `/\\r?\\n/` split.\n- Byte counting via `Buffer.byteLength(raw, 'utf8')` — correct for multibyte UTF-8.\n- Tie-breaking: all top-N sorts and global oldest/newest use `id` ascending as the secondary key for determinism.\n- Global oldest/newest: null when no stream has any parseable ts.\n\n**Edge cases covered:** empty streams array, empty raw string stream, single stream, single-entry stream, stream with zero parseable ts (null oldest/newest), CRLF line endings, whitespace-only lines (not counted), topN default (>5 streams → 5 returned), topN=0 (empty arrays), topN>count (all returned), negative topN (clamped to 0), fractional topN (floored), multibyte UTF-8 byte counting (emoji + accented chars + Japanese), global ts tie-breaking by id.\n\n**Test result:** 31 tests passed, 1 test file. Coverage: 100% statements (55/55), 100% branches (48/48), 100% functions (5/5), 100% lines (54/54).\n\n**NOTE for orchestrator:** Project vitest.config.ts uses `include: [\"tests/**/*.spec.ts\"]` so the test file was created as `tests/unit/core/history/history-storage-stats.spec.ts` (not .test.ts). Verification command: `npx vitest run tests/unit/core/history/history-storage-stats.spec.ts`"
close_reason: "Shipped pm stats --storage aggregate history-stream metrics (total_streams/lines/bytes, largest_by_bytes + deepest_by_lines top-N, global oldest/newest) via pure core/history/history-storage-stats.ts. 31 module tests (100%) + command test + manual e2e. Per-item 'pm history --stats' folded into pm stats --storage."
body: ""
